claim.claim-text:
1. A communication device (103-1) comprising:
a processor (208) and a communication interface (228), the processor (208) enabled to:
receive a call via the communication interface (228);
determine whether the communication device (103-1) is active;
when the communication device (103-1) is inactive, determine that a second device (103-2) is active by transmitting a query to the second device (103-2) and receiving a response thereto; and
transmit a notification of the call to the second device (103-2), wherein the notification is enabled to trigger a selectable option displayed at the second device (103-2) for transferring the call to the second device (103-2).

13. A computer program product, comprising a computer usable medium having a computer readable program code adapted to be executed to implement a method comprising:
at a communication device (103-1) comprising a processor (208) and a communication interface (228), receiving a call for the communication device (103-1) via the communication interface (228);
determining, at the processor (208), that a second device (103-2) is active;
when the communication device (103-1) is inactive, determining that a second device (103-2) is active by transmitting a query to the second device (103-2) and receiving a response thereto; and,
transmitting a notification of the call to the second device (103-2), wherein the notification is enabled to trigger a selectable option displayed at the second device (103-2) for transferring the call to the second device (103-2).
